reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Very happy with my purchase. This bag is made very well and looks great. There's a lot of room with tons of pockets. Will be great for travel and work.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Right now this is my wife’s favorite tote, and she’s got so many I call her the bag lady. It’s priced right and perfectly sized. You can throw your laptop in it, and still have room for whatever else you want with no problem.Outside, the look is classy and “designer”. The white stitching is absolutely perfect, and the thread they used is thick and rugged looking. The bottom collapses flat in the center for storage, but flares out enough to stand on its own even when empty.It also has 3/8” tall brass ‘feet’ that keep your bag’s fabric from touching the floor. So if you go into the bathroom or some other nasty place, you can set the bag down without the fabric touching anything disgusting.There’s a zippered pocket on one side, and a little strap pocket to slip over your rolling luggage’s extended handle on the other. The carry handles on this are wrapped with vegan leather, and very thick. The shoulder strap clips on and off with easy-to-actuate metal clips, and it’s wide enough to be comfortable even with a full load.The inside is very nicely lined with a silky kind of material. Lots of pockets, padding, and zippers. Everything is sewn perfectly, with plenty of reinforcement. Even the top corners have pieces of vegan leather riveted over them for added protection. (It looks great, too.)My wife really likes the square metal rings that allow the handles to fall to the side, instead of sticking up. It’s a small thing, but something that bugged her about another tote she has.The little clutch it comes with is also nicer than expected. It’s made of the same materials, and has the same decorative accents as the big bag. The clutch has a removable wrist strap.Hope this helps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits a business view and useful
reviews.reviewText: I got this for my mom who runs her own business and is constantly running around with her laptop and other items she needs. This bag allows her to carry her laptop as well as additional documents and other things she may need easily while still looking professional unlike a backpack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Holds it all; slides on suitcase
reviews.reviewText: I was honestly so pleasantly surprised with this bag. I was mostly impressed with the design of it and how useful it was made. It easily fits my 13 inch laptop with plenty of room for folders, notepads, etc. I put my water bottle down and snacks in the second inside compartment. There are two outside zippered compartments. One is a smaller one that would be perfect for a cell phone and the other is a large one for whatever else you might need to carry. There are two separated inside compartments (Bo zipper for your laptop etc, as well as a divider that has its own cushion pouch. There is also an inside zipper compartment that would hold a Kindle or other reader. There are slots for pens as well. An outside strap fits over rolling suitcases, so that you don’t have something else to carry on your arm. They really thought of everything. So impressive. The only reason I did not give it five stars is that the quality of the zippers is just So so. They do tend to get a little bit of a wave in them and sometimes get a tad sticky, but not too bad. Overall, I would definitely order it again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The look of this bag is definitely executive/classy. It seems a little heavy to me while empty, but after I use it a few times, I'll let you know if my opinion changes. There are many zippers and compartments, which I love because I bring this to work each day and include a snack, lunch, water bottle & paperwork. I need to keep my work papers separate from the food items and this back does the trick. It has two outside zippered pockets, two sections inside, one large and two smaller pockets inside and two pen holders. ALSO, it came with a little black matching wristlet (not so small for a wristlet: 8 1/2" x 6"). It has 6 slots to hold credit cards, etc. Both bags are made from a black, tightly weaved fabric - very lovely!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for our laptop
reviews.reviewText: This laptop bag fits our laptop perfectly, protecting it from damage. The bag has a sturdy construction. The handles, zippers, and material are strong, and the craftsmanship is high quality. The seams are all evenly sewn with no gaps or puckers. The zippers operate smoothly. There is a surprising amount of room for it being such a sleek, narrow design. I can put all the cords, accessories, and laptop in their place and secure them from movement inside the case. For as sturdy as it is, it is surprisingly lightweight. This makes it easy to carry as it doesn't cause the shoulder strap to bite the skin. The smaller handles are perfect for hand carrying the bag and doesn't fatigue the wrist or shoulder. I am very happy I ordered this bag, and I would order this bag again!

reviews.reviewText: Love the clean minimalist design with the deep black canvas structure and white stitching. The large capacity bag does not look oversized. The padding inside bag help protect the laptop and other items. This laptop bag has a designer look and it made to withstand many traveling trips.
